Personal thoughts on the market: 
$SPY is hitting ATH yet small caps are being hit the hardest. Statistically, small caps perform poorly in Q2 and Q3, but large/mid caps either stay neutral or perform positively. From the start of the pandemic up until March of this year the markets were easy to predict and everyone (new and experienced) were making gains as if this was a normal thing in the market. 
People know that most of my posts are in relation to small caps because of the high volatility and low float. The small cap market will start heating up again heading towards Q4 and Q1 but if you decide to take swings be sure to stay disciplined with your risk reward ratio and know when to mentally stop out of your position. Small caps are already oversold IMHO, but there is no consistent momentum follow through so be patient and strictly stick to your plan! Never place all your eggs in one basket. It is close to impossible to call the bottom, but you can dollar cost average during fear.
